Defendant Eduardo Sandoval appeared by video, in custody.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by ADA Samuel Berg. Atty. MacKenzie Renner appears for Public Defender's office. Record by Atty. Renner as to status of representation. Defendant qualifies for public defender but they have not gotten an attorney assigned yet. Request to set initial appearance over until next week so defendant can appear with counsel. Court grants request.
Initial appearance scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Eduardo Sandoval appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Grace Hagerman appearing for Eduardo Sandoval. Attorney J.J. Crawford appearing for the State of Wisconsin. Court inquired if victim wished to be heard; no statement made. Defendant qualifies for State Public Defender. Pretrial assessment rates as High risk assessment.  Bond remains. Minutes filed.
Adjourned order to show cause hearing scheduled for September 23, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
Cash bond filed. Defendant refused to sign.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol. Defendant is not to enter any bars, taverns, or liquor stores. Defendant shall have "0" blood alcohol in his/her body whenever driving/operating a motor vehicle. Defendant shall not drive a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license. Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Defendant is to be booked and printed within twenty-four (24) hours. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH M.G. OR RESIDENCE. Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.
